verb.description: Grow or cause to grow and become more mature, advanced, or elaborate.
examples: motion pictures developed into mass entertainment
entrepreneurs develop their skills through trial and error

verb.description: Start to exist, experience, or possess.
examples: I developed an interest in law
a head injury that caused him to develop a rare form of memory loss

verb.description: Treat (a photographic film) with chemicals to make a visible image.
Bring (a piece) into play from its initial position on a player's back rank.

origin: Mid 17th century (in the sense unfold, unfurl): from French développer, based on Latin dis- un- + a second element of unknown origin found also in envelop.
